# Next.js Standards

Preferred product stack: **Next.js 16 App Router**.

## Critical

This Next.js may differ from training data. Before using unfamiliar APIs, read `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` and heed `AGENTS.md`.

## Conventions

- `app/**/page.tsx` stays thin — data + module page component
- Route groups for shells: `(auth)`, `(shell)`, operational, print, public
- Prefer Server Components by default; client only for interactivity
- Mutations via server actions; `revalidatePath` after writes
- Session edge gate via project’s `proxy.ts` / middleware — follow the repo

## Do not

Invent Pages Router patterns, outdated middleware APIs, or parallel data-fetch styles that fight the module architecture.
